# graphify generated artifacts — the whole dir is regenerated by code-only
# rebuild (git hook / `/graphify`), so ignore it wholesale rather than listing
# files: newer graphifyy versions keep adding artifacts (manifest.json,
# .graphify_labels.json, .graphify_root, …) that a per-file list silently
# misses. Untracked so rebuild churn can't dirty the tree and block
# checkout/merge. If absent, regenerate locally (graphify in .venv [dev] extra).
graphify-out/

# Claude Code session artifacts
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.superpowers/

